description:
The stunning apartment has been furnished to a very high standard and occupies a great position with Meadows view - tenancy includes underground private parking.

The accommodation comprises: a bright and airy open plan kitchen/living room including dishwasher, dining table and chairs. A double bedroom with built in wardrobes and bathroom with under floor heating.

The property further benefits from sliding doors, gas central heating and private underground parking which is included in monthly rental amount.

SITUATION
Simpson Loan is situated in the prestigious ‘Quartermile’ development off Lauriston Place, less than 1 mile south of the city center. The property is extremely well placed for those working in the central business district or for those at the University of Edinburgh, both of which are a stone’s throw away.

Sat on the edge of beautiful ‘Meadows’, the property is in an enviable position with so much open space right on its doorstep, however historic tourist attractions such as the Grassmarket and the Edinburgh’s Old Town are only a few minutes walk away as is the fashionable West End and George Street, with their cosmopolitan bars, restaurants and bespoke shops. Also within walking distance is the city’s cultural quarter: the Traverse Theatre, Lyceum, Usher Hall, Cameo and Filmhouse independent cinemas as well as all the trendy cafes and boutiques of Bruntsfield and Morningside.

The ‘Quartermile’ development itself offers numerous facilities including Peter’s Yard Coffee House, a Pure 24 hour gym, a Starbucks coffee shop and a Sainsbury’s supermarket.

Please note this space is only available for residents of blocks 1-12 Quartermile.

summary: BOOK A VIEWING AT 1LET.CO.UK Spacious and well proportioned two bedroom, unfurnished flat in the heart of popular Bruntsfield area of the city.
description:
BOOK A VIEWING AT 1LET.CO.UK

Spacious and well proportioned two bedroom, unfurnished flat in the heart of popular Bruntsfield area of the city. The flat is located within close proximity to The Meadows and Bruntsfield links with plenty of artisan cafes and shops nearby.


This property is located on the first floor of a traditional tenement building boasting traditional interior features such as cornicing and high ceilings throughout. Offering bright, well-proportioned accommodation, the flat benefits from gas central heating and secondary glazed windows and is secured by an entrance system.

The property comprises an entrance hallway with two cupboards (one with washing machine); a well-lit and spacious living room with bay window overlooking Bruntsfield Avenue and features a shelved alcove, ceiling cornicing and a fireplace.; the kitchen is fitted with a range of modern base and wall units with oven, hob, hood and fridge/freezer; two good sized double bedrooms and a bathroom with shower over the bath and window.

Externally the property boasts a well maintained shared garden to the rear which is fully enclosed.

The Bruntsfield area is perfectly placed for a number of social and recreational amenities including numerous shops, a main post office, bars, bistros, coffee shops and banks. A variety of recreational pursuits are available within the immediate vicinity including tennis and golf and the popular Meadows area is a short walk away. The area is well known for its fine schooling, from primary to secondary education including George Watson’s College, Edinburgh University and Napier University. There is easy access to and from the city centre either by car or by public transport. There is also easy access to the city by-pass for those looking to commute to the motorway network and Edinburgh International Airport. EPC rating: C. Landlord Registration Number: 402187/230/02041. Letting Agent Registration Number: LARN1806013.

summary: **Walkthrough Tour Available** Available now unfurnished 2 double bedroom flat.
description:
**Walkthrough Tour Available** Available now unfurnished 2 double bedroom flat.

The front door opens into the living room that has twin, south east facing, windows, a half-height built-in cupboard and retains its original hearth. The newly renovated kitchen adjoins the living room, as does the inner hall. The inner hall gives access to the two virtually identically sized double bedrooms that each have a double and a single built-in wardrobe. The right hand bedroom has a small, pitched roof, timber built extension, overlooking the back garden. A naturally lit shower room with three piece suite completes the accommodation.

The windows are double glazed and there is gas fired central heating.

There are both private front and back gardens. The front garden is lawned with borders planted with shrubs and perennials and has a perimeter hedge while the back garden also has a lawn and borders and a wooden boundary fence. There is also a communal grassed drying green to the rear.

Area:
Balgreen is a popular residential area of Edinburgh, adjacent to Murrayfield, and some three miles west of the city centre.

The area is well served by local shops that supply the day-to-day essentials; the Asda Chesser Supercentre is on New Mart Road and the Edinburgh West Retail Park on Chesser Avenue has an Aldi and an M&S Food Hall, while the Gyle Shopping Centre is conveniently located a short distance away.

Saughton Rose Gardens, Carrick Knowe Golf Course, Corstorphine Hill, Edinburgh Zoo and Murrayfield Stadium are all on the doorstep.

There are good bus services into the city centre and Balgreen has its own tram stop. Access to the central belt motorway network, Edinburgh International Airport and the Queensferry Crossing are all simply achieved. EPC rating: D. Landlord Registration Number: 1647901/230/31082.
